<item>
            <title>[JCR-747] TCK: observation tests are too restrictive</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-747</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The basic sequence in all observation tests is:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1) add listener&lt;br/&gt;
2) modify workspace&lt;br/&gt;
3) remove listener&lt;br/&gt;
4) wait for events on listener&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This sequence forces an implementation to maintain a logical order for listener registrations and content changes. In the light of the asynchronous nature of observation events this seems too restrictive for certain implementations.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The sequence should be changed to:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1) add listener&lt;br/&gt;
2) modify workspace&lt;br/&gt;
3) wait for events on listener&lt;br/&gt;
4) remove listener&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Which is also more intuitive from a user perspective.</description>
